name: Oklahoma
absentee_method: Released as a precinct as first report of the night
nyt_race_description_race: Representative Kendra Horn, a Democrat whose victory two years ago was one of the biggest upsets of the midterm elections, is running for re-election against Stephanie Bice, a Republican state senator. The district includes Oklahoma City, and the race is one of the most competitive in the country.
poll_display_race: Polls close at 8 p.m. Eastern time.
